<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Thomson, John. Journal, Mackenzie River, 1800-1802. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0021</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday the 14<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  La Violette set more snares<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> he took 1 hare<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Sunday the 16<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The young Man brought 16 Hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Monday the 17<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The River is frozen over opposite here.  <span class="AddHand-editors">[G]</span>ave Martin a piece of a Lodge value about one Skin, he offered to pay for it, but it being of so little value I thought it best to make him a present of it<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tuesday the 18<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  La Beccasse came from the Little Chiefs armed Bag &amp; Baggage.  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he latter were not able to feed him any longer, as they do not set sew take enough to feed themselves<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednesday the 19<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I this morning, scraped together all the Bits of Dried Meat &amp;<sup>c</sup> which served the Men for this days allowances &#8211; there is still one Bag of Pemican remaining which I have made a shift to preserve untill now &#8211; &amp; would wish much not to be obliged to break upon it unless it be for particular use<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Late in the afternoon 6 Men &amp; 4 Boys arrived, gave them tobacco and Drams &#8211; they slept only 2 nights to come from where Cens Sols is<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Little Chiefs Brother in law whom I sent in search of the Big Chief is one of them<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he latter <span class="AddHand-author">he</span> says is such a great ways off that he turned back after having sent S<sup>t</sup> André along with 2 y Men to tell him the news<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Received 60 Skins Credits &amp; Traded 14 Skins, 6 Skins Dry Meat, 2 of fatt<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> 3 of grease &amp; one white fish<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thursday the 20<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Gave out 120 skins on Credit, &amp; made a present of a small knife &amp; an awl to the old Basbue as encouragement to work well &amp;<sup>c</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the morning they went away, sent La Becasse along with them to pass the Winter, gave him 2 foot Tob<sup>c</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> a Dram<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> 5 hares &amp; about 2 skins Dry Meat<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Kept a young Man to hunt hares, sent him off immediately to set his Snares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Little blind Chief came &amp; paid me a vissit<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the afternoon a young came for Tobacco for the arrival as he said of 4 Men, sent him back with 9 Inches<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:right;">a</p>

